RIYADH: Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed Bin Salman congratulated Saturday Japan’s prime minister on his re-election. In a statement issued by state agency SPA, Salman congratulated Fumio Kishida on the occasion of his re-election as Japan’s Prime Minister, wishing him “every success and the friendly people of Japan steady progress and prosperity.” Kishida was re-elected as Japan's Prime Minister on Wednesday after his governing party scored a major victory in key parliamentary elections.